TriPR-ABSA

This repository is an independent research fork of TextGT:
https://github.com/shuoyinn/TextGT

The upstream TextGT implementation is Copyright (c) 2024 Shuo Yin and is
distributed under the MIT License included in this repository.

The 2026 modifications, published as TriPR-ABSA, add three pragmatic residual
branches, a train-split phrase prior, logit-level composition, evaluation scripts,
visualizations, and documentation. The project uses TextGT-BERT as a baseline.
It is not endorsed by or affiliated with the upstream TextGT authors.

The MIT license covers the upstream software and this repository's software
modifications. Third-party datasets, pretrained models, and GloVe resources are
not relicensed by this repository; users must follow their original terms.

The TriPR-ABSA architecture and result figures are Copyright (c) 2026 by the
contributors named in AUTHORS.md. They are included for project documentation;
reuse outside this repository requires permission from the relevant contributor.

Upstream paper:
Shuo Yin and Guoqiang Zhong. "TextGT: A Double-View Graph Transformer on Text
for Aspect-Based Sentiment Analysis." AAAI 2024.
